Phase 5: Cobertura Reporter Implementation

Created src/gd_tools/coverage/cobertura_reporter.py:
- generate_cobertura_report(plan, data, output_path) -> Path: Writes Cobertura XML using xml.etree.ElementTree
  - Builds <coverage> root with line-rate, branch-rate, lines-covered, lines-valid, branches-covered, branches-valid
  - Structure: <coverage> -> <packages> -> <package> -> <classes> -> <class> per file -> <lines> -> <line>
  - Each <line> has: number, hits, branch (true/false)
  - Branch lines also have condition-coverage attribute (e.g., '100% (1/1)' or '0% (0/1)')
  - Per-class line-rate and branch-rate attributes
  - Zero-coverage files included with all hits=0
  - Uses ET.indent for pretty-printing, xml declaration included

Created tests/unit/test_cobertura_reporter.py (8 tests):
1. XML well-formed (parseable by ElementTree)
2. Root <coverage> with line-rate and branch-rate attributes
3. <class> per file with correct filenames
4. <line> elements with number, hits, branch attributes
5. Branch lines have condition-coverage, statement lines do not
6. Zero-coverage files included with all hits=0
7. Rates match computed metrics (line-rate=0.625, branch-rate=0.333 for partial)
8. Per-file hits verified (player.gd and enemy.gd separately)

Updated reporter.py: generate_report() now calls real generate_cobertura_report() for cobertura format (was stub)

